SPARTA VTK dump examples
========================

These example scripts exercise the dump styles in the VTK package,
which write native VTK files (readable directly by ParaView or VisIt):

  in.vtk      2d flow around a circle (particles, grid cells, surf lines)
  in.vtk.3d   3d flow around a sphere (grid voxels, surf triangles)

They require SPARTA to be built with the VTK package and an external
VTK library (see doc/Section_packages.html #VTK and doc/dump_vtk.html).
If SPARTA was built without the VTK package, the "particle/vtk",
"grid/vtk", and "surf/vtk" dump styles are unavailable and these
scripts will stop with an "Unrecognized dump style" error.

Run (serial or parallel):

  spa_vtk -in in.vtk
  mpirun -np 4 spa_vtk -in in.vtk

Each run writes a series of per-timestep files:

  tmp.particle.*.vtu   particle points with id/type/velocity point data
  tmp.grid.*.vtu       grid cells (pixels in 2d, voxels in 3d) with cell data
  tmp.surf.*.vtp       surface elements (lines in 2d, triangles in 3d)

For a parallel run, add a '%' to the file name (e.g. tmp.grid.%.*.vtu)
to write one piece file per processor plus a .pvtu/.pvtp summary file;
open the summary file in ParaView to load the full domain.

Open any of the .vtu/.vtp/.pvtu/.pvtp files in ParaView.  Color the
grid cells by "proc" to see the domain decomposition, or by "vol" to
see the flow volume; color particles by "type"; use the velocity "v"
vector for glyphs.
